<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7918663>
    dc:description "Figs 1–9. Heriaeus spp., habitus:(1) Heriaeus sp. long spiniform abdominal setae; (2) H.allenjonesi antoni sp. n. female; (3) H.antoni sp. n. female; (4) H.copricola sp. n. male; (5) H. crassispinus Lawrence, 1942 male; (6) H. foordi sp. n. male; (7) H. latifrons Lessert, 1919 female; (8) H.madagascar sp. n. male; (9) H. muizenberg sp. n. female." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7918663/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7918667>
    dc:description "Figs 14–21. (14–17) Heriaeus allenjonesi sp. n.: (14) male palp, ventral view; (15) male palp, lateral view; (16) epigyne,ventral view;(17) epigyne, dorsal view;(18–21) Heriaeus antonisp.n.: (18) male palp, ventral view; (19) male palp, lateral view; (20) epigyne, ventral view; (21) epigyne, dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7918667/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7918671>
    dc:description "Figs 30–36.(30–33) Heriaeus foordi sp. n.: (30) male palp, ventral view; (31) male palp, lateral view; (32) epigyne, ventral view; (33) epigyne, dorsal view; (34) Heriaeus latifrons Lessert, 1919, epigyne, ventral view; (35, 36) Heriaeus madagascar sp. n.: (35) male palp, ventral view; (36) male palp, lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7918671/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7918665>
    dc:description "Figs 10–13. Heriaeus spp., habitus: (10) H. peterwebbi sp. n. female; (11) H. transvaalicus Simon, 1895 female; (12) H. xanderi sp. n. female; (13) H. zanii sp. n. female." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7918665/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7918669>
    dc:description "Figs 22–29. (22–25) Heriaeus copricola sp. n.: (22) male palp, ventral view; (23) male palp, lateral view; (24) epigyne, ventral view; (25) epigyne, dorsal view; (26–29) Heriaeus crassispinus Lawrence, 1942: (26) male palp, ventral view; (27) male palp, lateral view; (28) epigyne, ventral view; (29) epigyne, dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7918669/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

